bmit evidence for consideration.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">We have long called for fiscal and wider devolution to London and in the last year have embarked on joint work with the Mayor of London and the Core Cities to advance the case</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> for fiscal devolution to cities across England.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">This submission </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">addresses the following points, on which the Committee has invited views:</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="i" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 41pt; padding-left:13pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Organising Public Services</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. -  How public services, including employment, skills and welfare, should be organised t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">o complement devolution </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">- </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">W</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">e</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> believe there is strong evidence </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">which</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> demonstrates </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">that</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> devolution to London would lead </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">greater growth and improved public services.</span></li><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 41pt; padding-left:13pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Fiscal devolution –</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">How taxes and charges would be devolved  to provide a platform for growth- </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">W</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">e fully support the recommendations of the London Finance Commission and believe fiscal autonomy to be a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">critical foundation of greater growth.</span></li><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-indent:-28.39pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa